Module io.winterframework.mod.web
Package io.winterframework.mod.web

Interface WebRouter<A extends WebExchange>

Type Parameters:
A - the type of web exchange handled by the route
All Superinterfaces:
ExchangeHandler<Exchange>, Router<A,​WebRouter<A>,​WebRouteManager<A>,​WebRoute<A>,​Exchange>
public interface WebRouter<A extends WebExchange> extends Router<A,​WebRouter<A>,​WebRouteManager<A>,​WebRoute<A>,​Exchange>

A web router is used to handle HTTP requests.

It determines the web exchange handler to invoke based on the parameters of the request including the absolute path, the method, the content type and the accepted content type and language.

An web router is itself an exchange handler that can be used as root handler of a HTTP server.

1.0
